The first project of 2023 was an incredible one. A shoot for @cfmoto_usa which took us all over the southwest on a wild 4 day schedule with location changes mid day, weather issues, etc. Total dream project, tons of freedom and trust and a really good sense of team work putting all of our heads together for the end goal of perfection. 

After chatting with my friend @anthonyjaska about working on prijexts together for a couple months, this was the first of many. The team is just full on dream team. I can’t wait to share more from this project.

I had the pleasure of photographing the @cfmoto_usa Model Year 24 Motorcycle Lineup back in August with one of my favorite teams, @rallystudio and director @anthonyjaska — We went all over Washington state and had the most amazing group of humans who all worked their tails off, and I’m quite stoked and proud of this giant body of work we made.  Featured here is the 450NK in all it’s glory.  I’ll be sharing work from this project one bike at a time.  I love my job, dagnabbit. Earlier this year I had the honor of creating new imagery for the legendary tire company @bfgoodrichtires and their incredibly tried and true Winter T/A KSI tire. I got to work side by side with my good bud @cadevlacos while he made the moving images part of this for a spot in Canada. Shot in the Tahoe zone, we had a wild storm one the days and got massive snow, while the other day was nice and bluebird. From production to talent to location to crew, these few days were very special and I’m so grateful to have spent time with friends old and new.
